{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Public inquiry into working conditions at Leicester\u2019s textiles factories",
        "additional_details": "However, there are concerns about illegal working conditions in the sector, which have been linked to the spread of COVID-19.\r\n\r\nWe want the government to ensure proper scrutiny is carried out over the fast fashion supply chain in Leicester (home to a third of the UK\u2019s fashion manufacturers and 10,000 workers).\r\n\r\nThis should investigate potential illegality and inform enforcement action to ensure legal, fair and humane practices in the city\u2019s factories: fair pay, legal contracts, no overcrowding, PPE, sick leave & holidays.\r\n",
        "background": "Leicester has a proud industrial heritage and strong links to the fashion sector. The city has over 1000 textiles factories, supplying many high street and well-known online brands. ",
